<HEADLINE> Pacific Group Wins UNICEF'S Maurice Pate Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Children's Fund on Monday presented the Maurice Pate award to
the Pacific Regional Human Rights Education resource Team (RRRT)
for its exceptional work in improving the legal and social status
of children and women in the Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The Maurice Pate award, named for UNICEF's first Executive
Director, is given annually to an individual, group or
institution displaying outstanding leadership in fulfilling
UNICEF's ideals.
</P>
<P>
The RRRT team is funded by the British Government's
Department for International Development, and consists of two
lawyers, a community development worker and four technical and
administrative staff.  
</P>
</TEXT>
