<HEADLINE> Pak, Iranian Officials Discuss Afghan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Foreign Secretary
Shamshad Ahmad met visiting Iranian Special Envoy on Afghanistan
Aleauddin Bourjerdi Monday and discussed with him the current
status of the Afghan peace process.
</P>
<P>
The latest on-going initiative under the auspices of the U.N.
and the Organization of Islamic Conference for restoration of
peace in Afghanistan was reviewed during the meeting, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Special Envoy arrived here Monday afternoon
accompanying Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharazi, who is here
on a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting between Shamshad and Bourjerdi, the sources
said that Pakistani and Iranian officials held in-depth
discussions on ways and means to push the Afghan peace process
forward.
</P>
<P>
The two sides stressed the need for Pakistan and Iran to
closely coordinate their efforts to promote peace process in the
war-torn country, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
They also expressed their satisfaction with the continuous
contacts between the two countries to find a peaceful solution to
the Afghanistan problem, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
