<HEADLINE> Chirac Receives Envoy of Indian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Monday received here the envoy of Indian Prime Minister Atal
Behari Vajpayee, Brajesh Mishara, at the Elysee presidential
palace, said the French presidential office.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Chirac again expressed the profound worry
of France and the international community over the nuclear tests
by India and Pakistan, as well as their impact on the future of
Asia and control of non-proliferation in the world.
</P>
<P>
He urged India to take "emergency measures to contribute to the
security of the region and the consolidation of the international
regime over nuclear non-proliferation."
</P>
<P>
For his part, Mishara delivered a letter from Vajpayee to
Chirac.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the French presidential advisor on diplomatic affairs
Jean-David Levitte and other French diplomats held talks with
Mishara.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine will meet with the
Indian envoy on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chirac has proposed holding an international conference on
preventing India and Pakistan from making more nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Washington Post last Friday, Chirac
suggested providing security guarantee for India and Pakistan, as
well as sending aid in civilian nuclear energy in exchange for
their promise not to conduct any more tests.
</P>
<P>
If held, the conference will be attended by all the major
powers of the world, as well as India and Pakistan.  
</P>
