rethinking of a trip to India and Pakistan after the two South
Asian countries detonated nuclear explosions last month, the White
House said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Mike McCurry, asked about Clinton's
scheduled visit to India and Pakistan, said the president was
assessing the situation to determine whether he will go ahead
with the original plans. "It's under review," McCurry said.
</P>
<P>
Clinton, who visits Texas on Tuesday, canceled plans to
spend the night in Dallas and instead will return to Washington
in order to meet on Wednesday morning with Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
