foreign ministers about the developments in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
"The situation with respect to India and Pakistan is a
difficult one. It is one that the president has instructed his
national security team to pay very close attention to," McCurry
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"The president feels it's very important for both India and
Pakistan to refrain from further provocative steps, to avoid
steps that would exacerbate the tensions that already exist," he
added.  
