one in the region, has responded with almost identical words to the
nuclear tests conducted by India and Pakistan, saying the tests
raise the risk of nuclear proliferation in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Senior Israeli officials said that the danger would be even
greater if Iran and Iraq have nuclear capability. Israel
successfully bombed a nuclear reactor in Iraq in 1981.
</P>
<P>
The Arab countries in the region are calling for reining in
Israel into the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty and the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, and putting its nuclear facilities
under arms inspections. 
