<HEADLINE> Maldivian President Puts Off Pakistan, India Visits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
president Gayoom, who is also Chairman of the South Asian
association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC), was due to arrive in
Pakistan Tuesday and India Sunday to round off his customary
visits to the capitals of the seven-nation grouping, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Gayoom decided to call off his visits after issuing a statement
on Monday in Male, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
"As the current chairman of SAARC, I call upon all parties
concerned to exercise maximum, and to make every possible effort
to contain the situation," the president said in the statement.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC convention requires its chairman to visit all member
countries before handing over the chairmanship to the next host.
Sri Lanka will host the 10th SAARC Summit in Colombo in July this
year.
</P>
<P>
The Maldivian president already visited Bangladesh, Bhutan
Nepal and Sri Lanka last month.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC, formed in December 1985, groups Bangladesh, Bhutan,
India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
