<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Digital Equipment Corporation
(DEC) of the US set up the largest systems integration joint
venture in China here today.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Founder Di Cheng Information Technology Corporation
Ltd. is an equally held joint venture between DEC and Beijing
Founder Electronics Corporation Ltd., the top local systems
integrator in China.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture puts together the market strengths of the two
companies in China. The total value of the markets combined is
estimated at 300 million yuan (about 36 million US
dollars). Founder alone occupies over 50 percent of China's
systems integration market for governmental institutions.
</P>
<P>
DEC sources said that the joint venture is to employ 1,000
people and hopes to achieve annual sales of 70 million US dollars
in two years.
</P>
<P>
At a signing ceremony for the joint venture agreement in the
Great Hall of the People here this afternoon, John Rando, senior
vice-president of DEC's Services Division, said that the joint
venture is definitely beneficial to both sides.
</P>
<P>
"The joint venture is a logical business step in DEC's
commitment to driving a world-class systems integration
organization that is able to respond to the needs of the global
market place," Rando said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zhaodong, president of Founder, said that the joint
venture is a strategic step that the company took to become one of
the top 500 companies in the world.
</P>
<P>
He said that Founder will take advantage of DEC's management
experience and expertise in network services and systems
integration so as to increase its competitiveness in the
international market.
</P>
<P>
"The joint venture will provide excellent services and
complete solutions to government, telecommunications,
bank, financial and manufacturing markets," he said.
</P>
