<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Yunnan Copper Industry
Co. Ltd., one of China's leading copper producers, today issued
108 million A-shares on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
On the first day of trading, 72.14 million shares changed
hands, with the per share price closing at 8.33 yuan (about one US
dollars), up 33 percent from the issue price.
</P>
<P>
The second Chinese copper producer listed on the stock market
in China, Yunnan Copper issued 120 million A-shares to domestic
investors in late April, raising 734.6 million yuan. The funds
will be used for the company's technical upgrading.
</P>
<P>
The company's board of directors predicted the company can make
total profits of 171.71 million yuan in 1998, a year-on-year rise
of 32 percent, with per-share earnings reaching 0.36 yuan.
</P>
<P>
China ranks third in copper reserves in the world. It is
also the world's largest copper importer, accounting for 10
percent of the world's copper consumption.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts say the listing of copper enterprises on the
stock market can help boost the country's copper
production. 
