<HEADLINE> China Stresses Pollution Control along Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The government stressed the
importance of pollution control along the Yangtze River today,
asking local governments, enterprises and residents to protect the
country's longest river.
</P>
<P>
The State Environmental Protection Administration (SEPA) and
the Ministry of Communications (MC) will launch a one-month
large-scale program along the river to improve local people's
environmental awareness, beginning today.
</P>
