The SEPA and the MC will also jointly inspect the
pollution-control efforts of the local governments, especially
along the Chongqing-Yichang and Wuhan-Shanghai sections of the river.
</P>
<P>
The two ministry-level departments asked local departments to
give wide publicity to the importance of pollution control along
the river in a notice.
</P>
<P>
The SEPA and the MC jointly issued a regulation at the
end of last year, asking provinces and cities along the Yangtze to
get rid of solid waste on the river banks and to strictly control
garbage dumping in the area.
</P>
<P>
The SEPA and the MC will inspect the local governments'
implementation of the regulation this month.
</P>
<P>
With the rapid development of the economy and shipping, the
number of ships has increased substantially on the Yangtze, at the
same time increasing the amount of garbage dumped in China's
longest river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
