are expected to be cancelled on Tuesday, the second consecutive
day of a strike by the pilots which reflects the anachronism of
the social and economic structure of the air company. The unions
of pilots and the management of Air France will resume talks
Tuesday afternoon which will be focused on the abolition of the
double standard of pays for the young and old pilots, and a deal
