<HEADLINE> Deng Theory Training Class for Senior CPC Members Ends (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The second training class on Deng
Xiaoping Theory and the guidelines laid down by the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) for members and
alternate members of the CPC Central Committee closed here today.
</P>
<P>
At the closing ceremony, Chinese President Jiang Zemin, also
general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, called on Party
members to overcome all difficulties and score new victories with
the correct guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials must make persistent efforts to study Deng
Xiaoping Theory, and play an exemplary role in studying the theory
and carrying out the tasks set by the 15th CPC National Congress,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The 15th CPC National Congress incorporated Deng Xiaoping
Theory into the Party Constitution, which is a practical move to
arm Party members with the theory, a fundamental program to
improve Party building under the new circumstances, and a pressing
need to push the cause of building Chinese-style socialism into the
21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
The study of Deng Xiaoping Theory should be combined with study
of the report of the 15th Congress, Jiang said, explaining that
the Congress made a novel and thorough explanation of Deng
Xiaoping Theory on the basis of summing up China's achievements
since the 14th CPC National Congress, analyzing the domestic and
international situations in the march toward the new century, and
reviewing the country's development in this century, particularly
over the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
"It indicates that our Party has achieved a new level of
understanding of Deng Xiaoping Theory," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, he noted, the Marxist style of combining
theory with practice must be carried on in the course of studying
Deng Xiaoping Theory. Such a style is a critical political issue
which is vital to the prosperity and success of the cause of the
Party.
</P>
<P>
The study of Marxism must be linked with the practical issues in
the country's reform, opening-up and modernization drive, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Since the introduction of the policies of reform and
opening-up, our Party has carried forward this fine style of
study, opened up new realms of Marxism and blazed a new trail for
the building of socialism with Chinese characteristics," Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed out that some leading officials still
maintain the bad habit of merely quoting Marxism out of context
and engaging in formalism, bad habits which hinder the
implementation of the Party's policies, tarnish the Party's
image, suffocate the Party's vitality and hamper the healthy
growth of Party members.
</P>
</TEXT>
