<HEADLINE> Sino-UNESCO Cooperation Very Effective, Says NPC Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said here
today that the cooperation between China and the United Nations
Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) as
"very effective".
</P>
<P>
Li Peng made the remark during a meeting with visiting UNESCO
Assistant Director-General Colin Power, who is in charge of
education programs of the organization, and his party at the Great
Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
Li said the Chinese side appreciates the prolonged efforts made
by Power to enhance the cooperation between UNESCO and China.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to its cooperation with UNESCO
and bilateral collaboration in the areas of basic education,
vocational education, adult education, elimination of illiteracy
and higher education have been "very effective" over the past
years, Li noted, adding that China will continue to actively
participate in the programs organized by UNESCO .
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he expressed the hope that Power would continue to
contribute to the UNESCO-China cooperations.
</P>
<P>
Power said that China is one of the most important partners of
UNESCO and the country's educational cause have registered great
progress over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
He told Li that the UNESCO would make continued effort to
reinforce its cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Power and his party are here on a visit to China as guests of
the Chinese Ministry of Education.  
