<HEADLINE> China Hopes for Permanent MFN Status: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that the United States
government and congress will take a positive attitude to granting
China permanent Most Favored Nation (MFN) trade status, instead of
repetitive annual review of the issue, a Foreign Ministry official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao told a routine
press conference that the US government's annual argument over
whether to grant China MFN benefits or not hinders the smooth
development of the economic and trade ties between the two
countries, and introduces unstable elements into bilateral ties
at the same time.
</P>
<P>
The granting of MFN status is a matter of mutual benefit, Zhu
pointed out, and the US should change its outdated practice as
early as possible and give China permanent MFN status, so as to
create a better atmosphere for improving relations between the two
countries. 
