<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Governments at all levels should
take practical measures to curb the making of false statistical
reports and ensure the authenticity of statistical figures, so as
to let statistical work play its due role in the national economy
and social development.
</P>
<P>
It should be regarded as an important part of the efforts to
improve the work style of the ruling Communist Party of China
(CPC) and the government and to fight corruption.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, member of the CPC Central Committee Political
Bureau and Vice-Premier, made the remarks at today's national
teleconference on publicizing the February circular issued by the
State Council General Office asking governments and Party
committees at all levels to deal with the problem.
</P>
<P>
Fake statistical reports have been detrimental to the healthy
development of national economy, the image of the Party and the
government, as well as the Party's good tradition and work style,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Supervisory departments should make greater efforts to handle
cases related to false statistical reports, and officials who have
profiteered from making such reports must be removed from their
posts, the vice-premier stressed. 
