<HEADLINE> Romario Ruled out of World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Romario was axed from the 22-member
Brazilian squad as the striker failed to recover from a calf
muscle injury sustained on May 6 in Brazil's training camp in Rio
de Janeiro, Brazil coach Mario Zagallo said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Emerson, a 22-year-old defensive midfielder of the German side
Bayer Leverkusen, was named by Zagallo as Romario's replacement.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old striker broke down in tears, saying he was
devastated as he faced the massed ranks of the Brazilian media.
</P>
<P>
"It's the biggest disappointment of my life, but this doesn't
mean I won't play for Brazil again," Romario said.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo, his deputy Zico, the team doctor and physiotherapist
decided Romario would not make full fitness.
</P>
<P>
Romario shook off his demons in the last year to pass the
strict Brazil medical exams to make the World Cup squad, but the
injury ruled him out. 
</P>
