<HEADLINE> HK's External Trade Increases in March 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's total exports
increased by 5.5 percent in March 1998 over the same month last
year while imports went up by 0.3 percent, the Census and
Statistics Department of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the department show that the volume of Hong
Kong's re-exports jumped by 6.2 percent in the month over a year
earlier while that of domestic exports rose by 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first three months of 1998 with the same period
last year, the volume of Hong Kong's re-exports was up by 2.5
percent while that of domestic exports decreased by 4.6 percent.
Taken together, the volume of total exports soared by 1.4 percent
and that of imports declined by 1.7 percent. 
</P>
