<HEADLINE> Mozambique: Police Rounds Up 79 Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican police have rounded
up 79 drug traffickers and seized 16.75 kilograms of Marijuana
and some narcotic injections in its code-named Colombia Operation
here, the National Police Service announced.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Abilio Quive made the announcement here
Monday, saying two drug supply bases have also been destroyed,
the Noticias newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Quive was quoted as saying that the operation was mainly
aimed at cracking down on the drug traffickers and users and
smashing up the supplying bases in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Quive pointed out that the 79 detainees will be interrogated
so that it can be decided how seriously each one has been
involved in drug dealing. Some of the detainees are Mozambicans.
And some others are from Tanzania, Nigeria, Malawi and Asia.
</P>
<P>
According to Quive, the crackdown operation has been
supported by the Mozambican armed forces because many of the drug
dealers are based in the military zones.
</P>
<P>
The police spokesman noted that the anti-drug operation will
go on at unlimited time since activities of drug traffickers and
drug users are still rampant in Maputo.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that in the last four years, more than 220
tons of various drugs had been transferred out of Mozambique
through the port, airports and postal parcels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
