<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Five-time French Open champion Steffi
Graf will be out of the WTA rankings to be released on Monday, the
first time since January 1983.
</P>
<P>
Graf played only two tournaments in the past 12 months because
of injuries, failing to meet the WTA rule that players have to
play three tournaments to hold a ranking.
</P>
<P>
She played only at Hanover and Indian Wells after her defeat in
the quarter-finals at Roland Garros last year against South
African Amanda Coetzer.
</P>
<P>
Graf, winner of 21 Grand Slam singles tiltes and 103
tournaments, first entered the ranking at 213 when she joined the
Tour as a 13-year-old.
</P>
<P>
The German champion, 29, hoped to be fit for her 13th Wimbledon
later this month, reigned as world number-one for a Tour record
374 weeks, including a run of 186 consecutive weeks from August
1987 to March 1991.
</P>
<P>
She underwent two operations on her left knee in 1997. 
</P>
