<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals in Macao Drop 8.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of visitors to Macao in
the first four months of the year dropped 8.4 percent from the
same period last year, the latest official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department on Tuesday, visitor arrivals added up to
2,434,083 during that period.
</P>
<P>
In April, the number of visitors came to 649,966, down 1
percent from a year earlier. However, it means a slight recovery
from March, when 578,181 tourists arrived.
</P>
<P>
The figures show that the number of Hong Kong visitors, which
accounted for some 70 percent of all arrivals, rose 6.5 percent
from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
But tourist arrivals from the Republic of Korea, Japan,
Southeast Asian nations and Europe all plummeted by as much as 84
percent.
</P>
<P>
The drop in tourist arrivals is considered a result of the
financial storms which broke out in Asia last year. Macao received
7 million tourists in 1997, down 14 percent from the previous
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
