the national team in April after a two-year break due to a knee
injury. He has since scored three goals in seven World Cup warmup
matches.
</P>
<P>
With 45 goals in 79 international matches, Hang also is the
country's most prolific scorer.
</P>
<P>
Lee Dong-kook, 19, became the youngest South Korean ever to
join the national soccer team as a next generation star.
</P>
<P>
Among the pick-ups, three play in the Japanese league, namely
forward Kim Do-hoon, midfielder Ha Seok-ju and defender Hong
Myung-bo.
</P>
<P>
Hong is considered as the best Asian defender with powerful
long-distance shots.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Seo Jung-won is coming from R.C. Strasbourg of the
French league, and Roh Jung-yoon from N.A.C. Breda of the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
In France, South Korea will meet Mexico, Belgium and the
Netherlands in the first round of the 32-nation World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Following are the roster:
</P>
<P>
Goalkeepers: Kim Byung-ji, Seo Dong-myung
</P>
<P>
