<HEADLINE> Three Bomb Blasts Reported in India's Assam State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Three successive bomb blasts in
Assam state, eastern India, Tuesday snapped rail and road links
between the northeastern areas and the rest of the country,
official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The explosions, carried out by the underground Bodo Liberation
Tiger (BLT), damaged a railway and two road bridges, severely
affecting rail and road traffic in the three districts of
Kokrajhar, Bongaigaon and Nalbari in the state, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
After the blasts, several express trains such as the down
Bangalore express, Calcutta-bound express and Delhi-bound express
were stopped along with other trains on their way, according to
the sources.
</P>
<P>
High civil, police and railway officials rushed to the sites
and efforts were being made to restore traffic within two days,
the sources said. 
