<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Illegal Bank Card Practices Banned in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC)
today issued a circular calling for an end to the practice of
using credit cards and other bank cards to defraud money from
residents.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the PBOC said that recently some people were found
to have been using bank cards and accounts to defraud funds from
residents in the capital of Beijing, the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region, the southwestern China city of Kunming, the northeastern
Dalian city and some other provinces, autonomous regions and
cities, which has not only seriously affected banks' normal
business but undermined banks' credit.
</P>
<P>
To protect China's financial order and the safety of residents'
money, the central bank has urged all commercial banks to handle
deposit business in strict compliance with the related
regulations. In handling bank card deposit businesses, the banks
must require depositors to produce their cards and codes,
otherwise the depositors' business applications will be turned
down.
</P>
<P>
Banks are empowered to reject depositors' business applications
whenever they found fund-raising illegal with bank cards, the
circular said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
