<HEADLINE> 25 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels Monday
fired mortars at government troops in northwest Kunchukkulam and
at least eight rebels were killed when the troops retaliated with
mortars and artillery, a military spokesman said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Government troops engaged in Operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain
Victory) commenced advancing last Wednesday and recaptured
Tunukkai Town and Vellayankulam west of Mankulam Town Monday. They
have taken full control of the Mallavi-Tunukkai byroad.
</P>
<P>
The government troops have surrounded Mankulam Town, which is
strategic for rebels, from the south, west and east, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said heavy fighting raged Monday, causing heavy
casualties on both sides. More than 17 rebels were killed in the
fighting.
</P>
<P>
Twelve soldiers were also killed while a group of soldiers are
reported to be missing in action.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a 15-year war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of Operation Jaya Sikuru was launched by the
troops on May 13 last year to open a key supply line along a
highway linking Vavuniya to the Jaffna peninsula in the north of
the island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
