<HEADLINE> Mordechai Arrives in Cairo for Talks With Mubarak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak
Mordechai arrived here Tuesday before noon on a lightning visit to
Egypt during which he will meet with President Hosni Mubarak, the
Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted by Defense and Military Production Minister
Mohamed Hussein Tantawi and Israeli Ambassador here Zvi Mazel.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai's visit to Cairo will focus on the Israeli proposal
to withdraw from South Lebanon, the strategic situation in the
Middle East and means of pushing forward the peace process,
especially on the Israeli-Palestinian track.
</P>
<P>
He will also discuss with Egyptian officials Cairo's endeavors
to bring closer Palestinian and Israeli stances as regards the
scope of the second stage redeployment from the Palestinian
territories.
</P>
<P>
He will explain to Egyptian officials the Israeli stance and
security requirements regarding the Israeli troop redeployment in
the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli peace talks have been stalled for more
than 14 months since Israel began work on a new Jewish settlement
in Arab East Jerusalem in March 1997.
</P>
<P>
Israel has rejected a latest U.S. proposal on a 13 percent
Israeli withdrawal from the West Bank, whereas the Palestinian
National Authority has accepted it.
</P>
<P>
Intensive contacts are now going on in Arab capitals in order
to work out an agreement on convening an Arab Summit to salvage
the peace process. 
</P>
