<HEADLINE> Agricultural Bank Plans More Housing Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Henan Provincial branch of
the Agricultural Bank of China (ABC) will extend 800 million yuan
in housing loans this year to help boost economic growth,
according to a bank official.
</P>
<P>
A total of 150 million yuan has already been issued to housing
buyers, the official added.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the smooth extension of housing loans, the branch has
formulated a number of documents on real estate development and
housing loans so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the branch will beef up loan supervision to make
sure that the loans are not used to develop luxury hotels, office
buildings, tourism resorts, high-class apartments or villas, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Many Chinese bank branches have decided to increase the amount
of housing loans in an effort to activate the housing sector and
thereby boost economic growth. The central government has selected
housing as one of the major driving forces for economic growth
this year.
</P>
<P>
China plans an economic growth rate of eight percent this
year. However, the growth of the gross domestic product slowed
down to 7.2 percent year-on-year in the first quarter of this
year, partly due to insufficient domestic spending and slumping
exports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
