<HEADLINE> ARATS Repeats Invitation to SEF to Visit Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-based Association For
Relations Across Taiwan Strait (ARATS) sent a letter to the Strait
Exchange Foundation (SEF) in Taiwan Monday, repeating its
invitation to SEF head Koo Chen-fu to visit the mainland.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that since early this year, ARATS has for
several times expressed its hope that Mr. Koo Chen-fu would lead a
delegation to visit the mainland or attend seminars or forums
jointly held by ARATS and SEF in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
SEF sent two letters to ARATS on Nov. 7, 1997 and Jan. 19 this
year, saying Mr. Koo would come "to visit in December or some time
later."
</P>
<P>
Responding to this, ARATS had invited SEF deputy
secretary-general to come to Beijing later April to make
arrangements for Mr. Koo's visit, including the time and subjects
for discussion.
</P>
<P>
"ARATS now reiterates it welcomes Mr. Koo Chen-fu to make a
scheduled visit at an earliest possible date. Please let us know
if SEF has any ideas about the meeting and its the time, venue and
subjects for discussion," the letter said.
</P>
<P>
In Monday's letter, ARATS thanked SEF for its invitation to
ARATS' deputy secretary-general to visit Taiwan and said the
deputy secretary-general would make the visit at an appropriate
time and after ARATS has chosen some appropriate exchange
programs.
</P>
<P>
The letter concluded by inviting SEF's deputy secretary-general
to visit the mainland on the same terms. 
