<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Redoubles Efforts Against Soil Erosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Hunan province in central China
has made strenuous efforts against soil erosion, treating 114
river valleys, and have controlled soil erosion on more than 3,000
square kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Facing worsening soil erosion because of large-scale
construction and development, the province has recently set forth
a goal of stopping soil erosion triggered by artificial factors by
the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
The province has a soil-erosion area of more than 47,000 square
kilometers, with more than 100 million tons of sand carried to the
Dongtinghu Lake each year.
</P>
<P>
A provincial land protection committee has been set up, and ten
percent of the province's water control construction fund is
allocated each year for land protection.
</P>
<P>
Surveys over the province's land protection and preliminary
research have been completed for land protection, and strict
regulations have been worked out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
