<DOCNO> XIE19980602.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rebound in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rebounded in Tokyo
Tuesday on near across-the-board buying that helped recoup a large
part of Monday's nearly 350-point plunge.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected First Section issues
on the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 233.42 points or 1.52 percent
from Monday's close to finish at 15,554.45.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, gained 16.27 points or 1.36 percent to reach
1,212.97.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the major section decreased to an estimated 280
million shares from Monday's 320 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nikko Securities was Tuesday's most heavily-traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Brokerage dealers covered their oversold positions, believing
buying by public and pension funds is firmly supporting the bottom
at around 15,000 for the Nikkei, traders said.
</P>
<P>
But there was no incentive to chase higher prices as persistent
selling from institutional investors in an attempt to reduce their
cross-shareholdings remained capping the top, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,335 issues listed on the First Section, gainers
outpaced losers 779 to 340, with 149 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
