<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Investigates Its Rural Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
initiated a massive investigation of the rural market in a bid to
find effective ways to expand rural demand and promote national
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the State Administration of Internal Trade said
that 12 working groups have been dispatched to different
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions to do the
investigation.
</P>
<P>
The investigation is designed to make clear the current
conditions of rural markets as well as their characteristics,
potentials and growing tendencies, and the findings will be used
to develop measures and policy proposals to promote rural markets.
</P>
<P>
The sources said market supply and demand conditions over the
past three years will be the key part of the investigation, which
mainly include the impact of market supply and demand, changes in
rural residents' incomes and their consuming ability, as well as
the characteristics and developing trends of consuming demands.
</P>
<P>
The operation of commercial enterprises will be another
important part covered by the investigation, which involves the
organizational patterns of commercial enterprises and their sales
channels and networks.
</P>
<P>
The investigation will also study the efforts made by local
governments and commercial departments in market development.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
