<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Take Measures for Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait is to take a package of
measures in an effort to build the country into a leading economic
and commercial center in the region.
</P>
<P>
According to local press reports Tuesday, Kuwaiti Crown Prince
and Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdallah said that a bill on the
measures will be submitted to the National Assembly with a couple
of months for approval.
</P>
<P>
Addressing hundreds of Kuwaiti dignitaries at a dinner banquet
monday, the crown prince said he was confident that by approving
and implementing the measures, Kuwait will "occupy a suitable
position" in the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
He said that the set-up of a free trade zone at Shuwaikh Port,
near Kuwait City, is the first step toward converting the country
into a free trade zone. This "will be followed by many measures to
stimulate the national economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said his government has instructed that procedures should be
simplified for issuing commercial licenses to allow foreign
businessmen easier access to the country.
</P>
<P>
Domestic fuel prices and public service charges are expected to
be raised to cut state budget deficit, he added. However, he
stressed that to accelerate economic reform needs "sincere
cooperation" of the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to the parliament's opposition to fuel price
hikes.
</P>
<P>
The parliament argued that the government should cut spending
first before making moves that aggravate the financial burden of
people with limited income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
