<HEADLINE> Oil Reserves at Oil-Bearing Stratum in Qaidam Basin Determined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese oil and geological experts
say that the newly-found oil-bearing stratum in Lenghu area of
Qaidam Basin, northwest China's Qinghai Province, contains 1.7
billion tons of oil and 300 billion cu m of natural gas.
</P>
<P>
In early May, Chinese oil workers discovered the
1,727-meter-thick oil-bearing structure, which spreads over 23,000
sq km, in the northwestern part of the basin.
</P>
<P>
An official from Qinghai Petroleum Administration said Lenghu
area, with its huge oil and gas reserves, has been listed as one
of the major sites for exploration by Qinghai Oilfield.
</P>
<P>
According to him, a number of wildcats and several exploration
wells will be sunk this year in Lenghu area. So far, necessary
geological preparations have been made and prospecting workers
have started sinking wells in some areas or testing oil and gas
reserves.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Oilfield, which was founded four decades ago, has
produced more than one million tons of crude annually in seven
consecutive years. It has verified more than four billion tons of
oil reserves and 150 billion cu m of gas reserves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
