<HEADLINE> Beijing Launches Training of Bosses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The labor department in the Chinese
capital city of Beijing has launched special training of those who
wish to become "bosses".
</P>
<P>
Such courses were held using the experience of France for the
implementation of re-employment training projects. Trainees expect
to run their own businesses after being trained, said Che Zhigang,
an official from the training center under the Beijing Municipal
Labor Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Che said that related training will be carried out in three
steps:
</P>
<P>
One month will be devoted to lectures by experts and professors
who will teach trainees on industry and commerce, taxation, market
management, and related laws and regulations. Two months will be
used by experts and professors to teach trainees how to become
"bosses", and during a five-month period later on, experts and
professors will offer consultation and guidance for trainees who
are running businesses independently.
</P>
<P>
To date, the first group of trainees have started businesses of
their own after theoretical studies. Most of the businesses are in
catering and services.
</P>
<P>
Che said that the number of people who apply for the training
courses is on the rise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
