<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fast Economic Growth Creates New Jobs in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Along with fast economic growth
and social progress, many new kinds of occupations such as
brokers, appraisers, community health workers and image designers
have emerged in Shanghai, the leading industrial and commercial
center in China.
</P>
<P>
The shaping of the market economy in the city is regarded as
the major factor behind the appearance of new professions.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the number of insurance salesmen in
the city has exceeded 11,000. Thanks to their efforts, more and
more Shanghai residents have bought insurance policies of
different kinds, with the total premium reaching 2.7 billion yuan
(325 million US dollars) in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has established more than 3,700 brokerage bodies
involving tens of thousands of people since 1992. These
organizations' business cover industrial products, real estate,
property rights, futures, technology, culture and sports.
</P>
<P>
A group of new occupations which are helpful to the improvement
of local residents' living quality have sprung up in tandem with
the growing income of their residents and the changes of their
consumption patterns.
</P>
<P>
Community doctors, household decoration designers, delivermen
of vegetables and table water are warmly welcomed by local
residents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
