<DOCNO> XIE19980602.0232 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Turning Mt. Qomolangma into Tourist Attraction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China is turning Mt. Qomolangma,
the world's highest peak which previously attracted mountain
climbers only, into a new holy land for tourists.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Tibet Tourism Bureau said that some 7,000
tourists from worldwide visited the mountain last year, and the
number is expected to increase this year.
</P>
<P>
Usually, tourists can reach the base camp located some 5,200
meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
When this reporter visited the mountain last month, he saw that
Japanese-made land cruisers used for carring tourists scattered
near climbers' tents. Tourists were posing for pictures, or
hailing toward the peak which is several miles away from the base
camp.
</P>
<P>
The weather was not cold, and many people wore T-shirts.
</P>
<P>
The best season to make the pilgrimage is early summer
or autumn, when there are no snowfall and heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
The peak is covered by snow, like a white bear sitting
calmly. The sky is blue and stunning, and the thawing ice is
musical.
</P>
<P>
"Mt. Everest is the world's roof. That is why I've come here,"
said Nathale Stirniman, from Sweden.
</P>
<P>
"You can't imagine how beautiful the scenery is before you
arrive at the foot of the mountain," said Todd McWhirter, a
tourist from the United States.
</P>
<P>
Cao Xiaoyu, director of the Beijing Office of the Tibet
Tourism Bureau, said that China is turning the mountain into one
of the most attractive tourist sites in the world.
</P>
<P>
A natural reserve has been set up in the mountain region where
foreign-invested hotels are expected to be built, she added.
</P>
<P>
Mt. Qomolangma, the North Pole and the South Pole are
called the world's Three Poles. But only the mountain can be
reached by ordinary people, according to Cao.
</P>
<P>
"The journey to the mountain is an adventure. However, no
serious accidents have so far occurred," she said.
</P>
<P>
She said that the mountain and the Tibet region warmly welcome
foreign tourists, and there is no restriction on them.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said that tourism industry is a key factor in
the economic development of Tibet, which is comparatively
backward.
</P>
<P>
Cao's office is a major organ in China to issue travel
permit for Tibet-bounded foreigners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980602.0233 </DOCNO>
