<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All People in Ethnic Region to be Accessible to Drinking Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Government of south China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region plans to provide clean water for all the
people in the region by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
By last year, the region had more than 3 million people who had
difficulties in drinking clean water. And late last year, it set
to solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
By now, some 940,000 people in 28 poor counties have begun to
enjoy drinking water, through efforts of drilling wells, building
diversion works and cisterns.
</P>
<P>
Due to stony mountains and irregular rainfall throughout the
year, Guangxi has long been plagued by a lack of water. So it is
known as a place that has "many mountains, limited water sources
and farmland".
</P>
<P>
Some people used to store rainwater for drinking, said a local
official, who is in charge of local poverty relief work, adding
that a lack of water costs local people more time and money, and
as a result, affects their efforts to get prosperous.
</P>
<P>
The official warned that weak awareness of environmental
protection is at the same time worsening the situation of water
shortage.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has decided to provide 55 million yuan
to help fulfill this year's water supply plan, aiming to offer
qualified drinking water to the remaining population in 53
counties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980602.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-02 06:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major New Items in Leading Israeli Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Israeli newspapers Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post
</P>
<P>
-- Defense officials Monday categorically rejected Pakistan's
charges that the Israeli Air Force had been on the verge of
striking from India its nuclear installations last week,
dismissing them as "nonsense, untrue, and completely baseless."
Pakistan had reportedly claimed that Israeli F-16s had landed in
India and were about to attack Pakistan's nuclear test sites
before the tests were conducted.
</P>
<P>
Maaretz
</P>
<P>
-- Arab countries could not reach agreement Monday on convening
a summit intended to press Israel to break the deadlock in the
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and Egypt are reluctant to have the summit to be held in
Damascus because they feared that Syria might call on all Arab
countries to freeze their ties with Israel. Several Arab countries
are also unwilling to attend a summit while the United States is
still mediating between Israel and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Yediot Aharonot
</P>
<P>
-- Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai departs for Cairo Tuesday
morning for a meeting with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak to
discuss the state of negotiations between Israel and the
Palestinians and an offer for an Israeli withdrawal from south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Several attempts made in recent months to initiate such a
meeting have failed because of the tension in Israeli-Egyptian
relations over the deadlocked peace process. 
