<HEADLINE> Dhaka Takes Steps to Boost Local Government Bodies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has taken
steps to strengthen local government bodies to ensure a better
life for the rural people.
</P>
<P>
"Villages are the life force of the nation and the government
has taken all possible steps for the development of rural areas by
strengthening the local government system," Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina told a conference attended by chairmen and members of union
councils here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Hasina was quoted by the local press Tuesday as saying the
government has decided to make the union councils more effective
and take steps to increase their economic power.
</P>
<P>
"The union councils are already working as the administrative
units (of the country)," she said, adding, "Their chairmen and
members will have to exercise their right with more skill and
efficiency."
</P>
<P>
In this regard, she stated, the government has started a
program with the help of the U.N. Development Program to train
union council chairmen and members.
</P>
<P>
The government has also increased the number of projects from
the original five to eight to be implemented by union councils,
she said.
</P>
<P>
She asked union council leaders to be on alert against
corruption during the implementation of the projects.
</P>
<P>
She also told the conference that steps have been taken to
increase the income sources of the union councils.
</P>
<P>
There are altogether 4,451 unions in this South Asian country.
</P>
</TEXT>
