<HEADLINE> 12 Still Missing in Accident in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people including 11 from
the same family are still missing after the truck they were
traveling in plunged into a river early Saturday morning in
Dhading district bordering the Kathmandu Valley, a senior police
officer said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated truck has also not been found, and the rescue
operation is still going on, said Gyanendra B. Mahat,
superintendent of police at the Valley Traffic Police Office.
</P>
<P>
The truck carrying 12 passengers was on its way to Kathmandu
when it suddenly plunged into the Trisuli river.
</P>
<P>
Sangmu Tamang, a 45-year-old woman, was rescued by fishermen
about one kilometer downstream. But her other family members
including the driver went missing and are feared dead.
</P>
<P>
The highway patrolling post was ordered Sunday to start the
rescue operation. 
</P>
