<HEADLINE> Albania Calls for International Intervention in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian government has called
on the international community to intervene to prevent a possible
bloody war at a time when thousands of ethnic Albanians are
flooding from the Serbian province of Kosovo into the northern
part of the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Monday, the Albanian government
attributed the new wave of refugees to the racial cleansing policy
implemented by the Belgrade authorities.
</P>
<P>
About 2,000 ethnic Albanian refugees have streamed from Kosovo
into Tropoja on the northern border of Albania and the number is
on the increase, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government calls on the U.S. government, European
Union, Contact Group member states and other international
organizations to intervene effectively and immediately to stop the
ethnic cleansing in Kosovo, as the cleansing could be a forerunner
of a bloody war, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement warned that the dialogue between the two
conflicting sides in Kosovo may come to a premature end under the
current precarious situation.
</P>
<P>
A few days ago, large-scale armed conflicts erupted in Kosovo,
inflicting casualties both on the Serbian police and the armed
ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
The Office of the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees in Kosovo
has decided to transport emergency supplies to the sheltering
region of refugees in northern Albania, the statement added.
</P>
</TEXT>
