<HEADLINE> Two Quakes Hit North Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Two earthquakes hit Zhangbei county
in northern part of Hebei Province, north China, this morning,
according to the China Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The first quake, measuring 4.6 on the Richter Scale, occurred
at 9:32 (Beijing time), and the second one measuring 4.0 occurred
at 10:47, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The epicenters were located at 41.1 degrees north latitude and
114.5 degrees east longitude, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
This was the strongest aftershock of the earthquake measuring
6.2 in Zhangbei on January 10, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
So far, there was no report of casualties, but some houses
collapsed, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The quake was felt in the northwestern part of Beijing, some
200 kilometers from Zhangbei. 
</P>
