<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Claims Over 800 Lives in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The fury of the blazing sun
claimed more than 100 lives in Orissa state in eastern India
during the past 24 hours bringing the death toll in the current
spell of heat wave sweeping parts of the country to more than 800,
The Hindustan Times reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Orissa continued to experience unprecedented heat wave
conditions with the mercury hovering above 46 degrees Celsius. The
death toll in the state this season has gone over 500.
</P>
<P>
Claiming that many deaths in interior areas and rural belts
were being left unreported, unofficial sources feared the actual
loss of lives in this eastern coastal state could have crossed
1,000, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people died of heat stroke in Uttar Pradesh while 10
deaths were reported from Rajasthan and 11 from Bihar states since
May 31. Two more people died in West Bengal, the paper further
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
