<HEADLINE> Czech, Italian Defense Chiefs Discuss Major Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Czech Defense Minister
Jaroslay Sedivy and his Italian counterpart, Beniamino Andreatta,
met on Monday to discuss a series of major issues, including the
crisis in the troubled Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta explained in detail Rome's policy towards the Balkan
region, where it is seeking to foster a collective reaction by
European states.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta said Italy recognized that the role played by NATO
there was an effective way to ease tension and offer a sense of
common security and defense cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The recently escalating tensions in South Asia in the wake of
separate nuclear tests by India and Pakistan were also a major
topic of discussion between the two defense ministers.
</P>
<P>
Sedivy urged a "new global approach to the policy of nuclear
non-proliferation" in reaction to the nuclear arms race between
India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Other bilateral issues the two discussed included exchanging
defense information and material between Italy and the Czech Republic
and the modernization process of the Czech armed forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
