<HEADLINE> Safin, Kournikova Crash out of French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Russian teenagers Marat Safin and
Anna Kournikova were both ousted from the quarter-finals at the
French Open tennis tournament here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Safin lost to home favourite Cedric Pioline in his third
five-setter, 7-5, 4-6, 6-7, 6-4, 6-4, while Kournikova was crushed
by third seed Jana Novotna from Czech Republic, 6-7, 6-3, 6-3, in
the women's contention.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Safin, who stormed past American Andre Agassi
and Brazilian holder Gustavo Kuerten, finally lost his three hours
18 minutes marathon match.  
