<HEADLINE> 11 Freight Cars Fall Into Danube in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Eleven freight cars at the rear
of a freight train fell into the Danube River Sunday when the
train was running on a railway bridge in Vodita, Romania.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian national television reported Monday night
that no one was injured in the accident.
</P>
<P>
Of the 47 freight cars, 11 fell into the Danube and two were
hanging on the bridge, one side of which was totally damaged.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers used cranes to remove the derailed cars from the
bridge and the river bed.
</P>
<P>
A railway administration official said railway traffic in the
region would be restored within 48 hours.
</P>
<P>
A special committee has been set up to investigate. The result
is expected to be announced in 10 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
