<HEADLINE> U.S. and Australia Sail to Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BREMEN, Germany, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Unites States and
Australia beat their last opponents in the second-run competition
on Monday to keep 6-0 records, advancing into the quarter-finals
of the Women's World Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
The Americans routed the Russians in a lopsided 96-60 game in
Bremen to top group E, while Australia edged defending champion
Brazil 76-75 for the first place in group F in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
WNBA star Lisa Leslie led the United States, who was third four
years ago in Australia, with a game-high 26 points and 7 rebonds.
</P>
<P>
Elena Balanova, who also played for WNBA last season, scored 12
points for Russia, which trailed all the way and was 30-52 at
halftime.
</P>
<P>
In other group E games earlier Monday, European champion
Lithuania also advanced to the last eight by defeating Spain 66-63.
</P>
<P>
Japan and China, which had the same record of two wins against
four losses, will take part in the four-team classification
matches with Germany and Hungary in Berlin from June 4.
</P>
<P>
In Berlin, Cuba beat Hungary 89-96 and Slovakia downed
Germany. The winners entered the quarter-finals. 
</P>
