<HEADLINE> Lithuania Beats Spian to Enter Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BREMEN, Germany, June 1 (Xinhua) -- European champion Lithuania
advanced to the quarter-finals after defeating Spain in a must-win
second-run group E game at the Women's World Basketball
Championship on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania's 66-63 victory over Spain put Japan, who posted a
2-4 record after its loss to China earlier Monday, to the fifth
place.
</P>
<P>
China (1-5) was sixth and disqualified for the last eight for
the first time since the 1990 Moscow Worlds where China placed
ninth.
</P>
<P>
Japan and China will take part in the four-team classification
matches with Germany and Hungary in Berlin from June 4.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania lagged from the very beginning and ended the first
half with 30-35.
</P>
<P>
During the first five minutes after the interval, Lithuania put
up a 9-4 run to make it 39-39.
</P>
<P>
The lead was exchanged for four times before center Jurgita
Streimikyte hit two baskets in the lane to put Lithuania 49-46
ahead.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania held off a late comeback from Spain, fourth place
finisher in the European championsihp, to come third in Group E.
</P>
<P>
Forward Jolanta Vilutyte tossed in 16 points for Lithuania and
Straeimikyte added 15.
</P>
<P>
Forward Anula Neves scored 17 points to pace Spain, which placed
fourth in Group with a 3-3 record.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Russia, both unbeaten in group E, will
clash late Monday for the top place.
</P>
<P>
In Berlin, Cuba beat Hungary 89-96 and Slovakia downed
Germany. The winners entered the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Cuba is 4-2 and second in Group F while 3-3 Slovakia is
fourth. The top place for the group will be decided between
Australia and Brazil late Monday. 
</P>
